sentences: Amina Claudine Myers (born March 21, 1942)  is an American jazz pianist, organist, vocalist, composer, and arranger.
Myers took piano and violin lessons, but eventually, partly for financial reasons, settled on the piano, taking weekly lessons of fifteen minutes each."
In her second year, she was invited to play at The Safari Room in Memphis, Tennessee.
After graduation, she moved in 1963 to Chicago, where she taught music at an elementary school.
In the late 1960s, Myers added "Amina" to her name.
In 1976 Myers relocated to New York City, where she intensified her compositional work and expanded it into the realm of Off-Broadway productions.
Around 1978 she began touring in Europe with the Lester Bowie Quintet and his New York Organ Ensemble.
